==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wollastons doublet
<hw>Wol"las*ton's dou"blet</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[After <person>W. H.
<etsep>Wollaston</etsep></person>, English physicist.]</ety>
<fld>(Optics)</fld> <def>A magnifying glass consisting of two
plano-convex lenses. It is designed to correct spherical aberration and
chromatic dispersion.</def> <note>Under "wollastonite" the eponymous
inventor is described as a chemist.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wolle</ent>⟦br⟧
